Release Notes .. :

Microsoft's latest release of the .NET Framework is 3.5. This release of the .NET Framework
is Microsoft's response to user needs for loosely-coupled, asynscronous, standards-based
applications that are easily built and maintained. In this QuickStart! course, Mark Long
introduces you to the technologies and new functionalities of .NET Framework 3.5.
He provides a brief introduction into the technologies, history, tools and resources for the
latest release of Microsoft's application development platform.
